[normal]Written evidence submitted by Zero Emissions Platform (CCS07)[bold]Founded in 2005, 
[normal]the Zero Emissions Platform (ZEP) 
[normal]serves as an advisor to the European Commission on the research, demonstration and deployment of 
[normal]CO
[normal]2
[normal] Capture and Storage
[normal] (CCS). 
[normal]ZEP is a
[normal] coalition of over 200 members from 19 countries – representing academics, scientists, 
[normal]European 
[normal]utilities, petroleum 
[normal]companies, equipment suppliers and environmental NGOs
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]SUMMARY[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]ZEP 
[normal]also 
[normal]recommends 
[normal]establishing up to six new CO
[normal]2
[normal] storage pilots
[normal] across Europe to complement demonstration projects
[normal] and 
[normal]accelerate state-of-the-art technology
[normal]. This 
[normal]will 
[normal]enable meaningful R&amp;D on a range of issues
[normal], 
[normal]which may then be used generically – on- 
[normal]and 
[normal]offshore. 
[normal]Qualifying and improving knowledge of 
[normal]representative
[normal] geological storage conditions will also greatly benefit the planning of a trans-national, European CO
[normal]2
[normal] transport infrastructure. 
[normal]In certain cases, the storage pilot may even be used to explore
[normal] industrial scale-storage in the same reservoir.
[normal]&#xa0;
